tags.string:
{string} config.projectId - The project ID from the Google Developer's
    Console. E.g. 'purple-grape-123'.
tags.name: config.projectId
tags.description: • The project ID from the Google Developer's Console. E.g. 'purple-grape-123'.

tags.string:
{string=} config.keyFilename - Full path to the a .json, .pem, or .p12
    key downloaded from the Google Developers Console. NOTE: .pem and .p12
    require you to specify `config.email` as well.
tags.name: config.keyFilename
tags.description:
• Full path to the a .json, .pem, or .p12 key downloaded from the Google Developers Console. NOTE: .pem and .p12
    require you to specify config.email as well.

tags.string:
{string=} config.email - Account email address. Required when using a
    .pem or .p12 keyFilename.
tags.name: config.email
tags.description: • Account email address. Required when using a .pem or .p12 keyFilename.

tags.string:
{boolean=} config.autoRetry - Automatically retry requests if the
    response is related to rate limits or certain intermittent server errors.
    We will exponentially backoff subsequent requests by default. (default:
    true)
tags.name: config.autoRetry
tags.description:
• Automatically retry requests if the response is related to rate limits or certain intermittent server errors.
    We will exponentially backoff subsequent requests by default. (default:
    true)

tags.string:
{number=} config.maxRetries - Maximum number of automatic retries
    attempted before returning the error. (default: 3)
tags.name: config.maxRetries
tags.description: • Maximum number of automatic retries attempted before returning the error. (default: 3)

tags.html:
var gcloud = require('gcloud')({
keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json',
projectId: 'my-project'
});

var dataset = gcloud.datastore.dataset();
// equal to:
// gcloud.datastore.dataset({
// keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json',
// projectId: 'my-project'
// });

var gcs = gcloud.storage();
var bucket = gcs.bucket({
name: 'PhotosBucket',
// properties may be overridden:
keyFilename: '/path/to/other/keyfile.json'
});

var gcloud = require('gcloud')({
keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json',
projectId: 'my-project',
maxRetries: 5 // retry rate limited requests 5 times before giving up
});

description.full:
There are two key ways to use the gcloud module.

  1. Provide connection & configuration details up-front.

  2. Provide them at the time of instantiation of sub-modules, e.g. a Datastore
    dataset, a Cloud Storage bucket, etc.

See our Authorization Guide for how to obtain the
necessary credentials for connecting to your project.

tags.html:
var gcloud = require('gcloud');
var bigquery = gcloud.bigquery({
projectId: 'project-id',
keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json'
});

description.full:
Analyze Big Data in the cloud with
Google BigQuery. Run fast, SQL-like
queries against multi-terabyte datasets in seconds. Scalable and easy to use,
BigQuery gives you real-time insights about your data.

tags.html:
var gcloud = require('gcloud');
var datastore = gcloud.datastore;
var dataset = datastore.dataset({
projectId: 'project-id',
keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json'
});

description.full:
Google Cloud Datastore is a fully
managed, schemaless database for storing non-relational data. Use this object
to create a Dataset to interact with your data, an "Int", and a "Double"
representation.

var pubsub = gcloud.pubsub({
projectId: 'project-id',
keyFilename: '/path/to/keyfile.json'
});

description.full:
Experimental

Google Cloud Pub/Sub is a
reliable, many-to-many, asynchronous messaging service from Google Cloud
Platform.

Note: Google Cloud Pub/Sub API is available as a Limited Preview and the
client library we provide is currently experimental. The API and/or the
client might be changed in backward-incompatible ways. This API is not
subject to any SLA or deprecation policy. Request to be whitelisted to use it
by filling the Limited Preview application form.
